===Etymology===
From {{af|en|year|book}}. Compare {{cog|fy|jierboek|t=yearbook}}, {{cog|nl|jaarboek|t=yearbook}}, {{cog|de|Jahrbuch|t=yearbook}}, {{cog|sv|årsbok|t=yearbook}}, {{cog|fo|árbók|t=annal, record}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vininn126-yearbook.wav|Audio (US)}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[reference]] [[book]], [[published]] [[annually]].
# {{lb|en|countable|US|education}} A [[publication]] [[compiled]] by the [[graduating]] [[class]] of a [[high school]] or [[college]], [[recording]] the [[year]]'s [[events]] and [[containing]] [[photograph]]s of [[student]]s and [[faculty]].
# {{lb|en|uncountable|US|education}} A [[school]] [[subject]] in which students learn [[journalistic]] skills by compiling a yearbook.
